it can gate, they were killed without the AG spells, so what did the AG line give us, nothing.  And again, I would like to see an upgrade which goes for the whole wizard class, level 1 to level 60, not the post 50 crowd.  I am currently walking away for 6 month to get rid of this headache.  Maybe by then I will be able to come back and enjoy the wizard class again.  Don't get me wrong, I have played my wizard for well over 2 years, but, recently, with the frustrations of grouping in any of the post 50 dungeons, wizards are not in any kind of demand, so I started a bard.  Got him to 40, and got him there quick with no need for endless LFG shouts.  I just wish my wizard could get groups that easy.  I have thought about retiring my wizard and playing the bard full time, but the wizard is what I wanted when I first started playing, and it is hard to walk away from the attention and love I have put into the class.  This 6 month break should hopefully give me a new insight to taking the wizard down from the shelf and dusting him off.  Maybe in 6 months time, VI will actually make the wizard a viable group option other than being the taxi cab ride out of areas after a battle.    <br>
